1. Definitions
   1.1. "Software" refers to the source code, binary code, documentation,
        and related materials for the project known as "SuperTable."
   1.2. "Licensor" refers to Kladna Soft Kft.
   1.3. "You" (or "Your") means the individual or entity exercising the
        rights granted under this License.
   1.4. "Small Organization" means any company, startup, or organization
        with ten (10) or fewer total employees, contractors, and agents,
        regardless of how many individuals access or use the Software.
   1.5. "Educational Use" means use by accredited educational institutions
        (schools, colleges, universities), students enrolled in such
        institutions, or educators for teaching, academic research, or
        coursework purposes.
   1.6. "Community Use" means use by registered non-profit organizations,
        open-source projects, or community groups for non-commercial
        purposes.
   1.7. "Enterprise Use" means use by any organization with more than
        ten (10) total employees, contractors, and agents, regardless
        of how many individuals access or use the Software, or use
        within a commercial product or service offered to third parties.

2. Grant of License

   2.1. Personal and Non-Commercial Use (FREE)
        You are granted a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive,
        non-transferable, perpetual license to download, install, and
        use the Software for personal, non-commercial purposes at no cost.

   2.2. Small Organization Use (FREE)
        Small Organizations are granted a worldwide, royalty-free,
        non-exclusive, non-transferable license to use the Software
        for internal business purposes at no cost, provided that:
        (a) The organization has ten (10) or fewer total employees,
            contractors, and agents (regardless of how many use the
            Software); and
        (b) The Software is not incorporated into a product or service
            sold or licensed to third parties.

        If Your organization grows beyond ten (10) employees, You must
        obtain an Enterprise License within thirty (30) days.

   2.3. Educational Use (FREE)
        Educational institutions, students, and educators are granted a
        worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive, non-transferable license
        to use the Software for Educational Use at no cost. This includes:
        (a) Classroom instruction and coursework;
        (b) Academic research and publications;
        (c) Student projects and thesis work;
        (d) Educational workshops and training.

        Educational Use does not include commercial training programs
        offered for profit.

   2.4. Community Use (FREE)
        Registered non-profit organizations and open-source projects are
        granted a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive, non-transferable
        license to use the Software for Community Use at no cost.

   2.5. Evaluation Use (FREE, TIME-LIMITED)
        Any entity may evaluate the Software for up to thirty (30) days
        to determine suitability for Enterprise Use. Extended evaluation
        periods require written authorization from the Licensor.

   2.6. Enterprise Use (PAID LICENSE REQUIRED)
        If You wish to use the Software:
        (a) Within an organization with more than ten (10) employees,
            contractors, or agents; or
        (b) As part of any commercial product or service provided to
            third parties; or
        (c) For commercial training programs offered for profit;
        You must obtain a separate Enterprise License from the Licensor.
        Contact the Licensor for pricing and terms.

